Text.Value: Don't be too hard on him. He was scared and missing home.
Those new recruits had better get here soon, or I'll drag them in from the Lower City myself.
We can't all run away and bury our heads in a burrow.
How embarrassing. Isn't it your job to catch criminals?
Says the one trespassing in our barracks. You're under arrest.

EditorData.NodeContext: Scorn/disbelief - how gullible do you think he is?

Text.Value: Attack.
That's impossible. Reynash was on duty the whole -

EditorData.NodeContext: Dismissive, stops short (about to say "night and day" when he realises

Text.Value: March yourself out of the room.
I'm a new recruit, just getting the lay of the fortress.
Leave.
Let him arrest you.
The thefts have been happening for a while?
I saw one of your officers acting suspiciously near that chest.
How's this? You leave now, and I won't arrest you for being in a restricted area.
What in the Nine bloody Hells is going on? Reynash?
I just caught another Fist trying to steal from you.
Appreciate the help you've given, but we need to get our shut-eye before we're back on duty. Civilian area is back the way you came.

EditorData.NodeContext: Firm - he's not going to negotiate on this

Text.Value: Get back out there and report to someone on duty! That's an order!
Attack.
Double duties, half rations, now we can't even get a moment of bloody shut-eye.
Probe the Fist's mind.
We're preparing for an invasion. You think we have time to go after petty thieves?
Ever since they ordered us to close the gates. He must have a nice little nest egg by now.
If he shows his face again, he's got a bed waiting in the cells.
I think a reward is customary for this kind of tip-off.
Now unless you want me pinning this on you - get out!
And you thought your first job was to go back to bed?
You've got one breath to explain why you're in here, or you're going straight to the cells.
That sneaky little git. It was him all along?
Allow him to escort you out.
An enemy spy! Weapons ready!
Attack.

Synopsis: This dialog happens when you encounter the Flaming Fist Thief in the Barracks area. If you wake the thief's colleagues his runs away and then one of the guards starts this dialog with you.
